A cool thing you buy in those days was the full source code for SPITBOL, =
on microfiche.  I bought a copy and a number of my friends did, too.  It =
was really beautiful code.

> On Aug 8, 2022, at 11:11 PM, Rob Pike <robpike@gmail.com> wrote:
>=20
> We're probably well off topic now but...
>=20
> Many years ago I ran into Bob Dewar on a visit to Cambridge University =
and we got to talking. He said that the original implementation of =
SPITBOL, for the System/360, was in assembler (of course), and written =
by him and Belcher (?). The story he told was that they wrote it all =
down first, put it on punch cards, and sent it to the IBM machine. The =
next day they got back a listing with a bunch of errors. They iterated. =
By the fourth round=E2=80=94fifth day=E2=80=94they had a working =
SPITBOL.
>=20
> I still marvel at the productivity and precision of his generation of =
programmers.
>=20
